<TITLE> Shops open till 10pm from Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 26 (bdnews24.com) Shops, malls and markets will remain open until 10pm from Wednesday for ease of shoppers during ongoing Ramadan. The announcement came after a meeting between prime minister Sheikh Hasina and Bangladesh Shop Owners Association in the morning. Association president Amir Hossain Khan told bdnews24.com that the meeting had decided that closing times for all shops and markets across the country would be extended until 10pm during Ramadan. The prime minister had earlier in the month directed shops to remain open until 10pm on Fridays and Saturdays instead of 8pm ahead of Ramadan. b
